Personal Information Received from the EU:
Integra LifeSciences (“Integra”) is certifying to the Safe Harbor principles for data as set forth below:
(1) 	Human Resources / Employee/Employment Data. Integra processes employee/employment personal data to comply with its legal obligations and to carry out and manage functions related to: 
(A)	Human Resources Administration:  to provide the services necessary to fairly evaluate and compensate current, past or prospective employees and comply with applicable employment laws;
(B)	Business Process Administration: to facilitate the efficient day-to-day running of business operations;
(C)	Safety and Security: to promote the safety and protection of employees, resources, and communities and comply with applicable safety and security laws;
(D)	Internal Audit: to manage compliance with Integra’s internal audit programs and applicable laws. 

(2) Clinical Trial Data.  Integra processes personal Information regarding patients located in the EU/EEA that is transferred to the US for customary and legitimate business purposes, such as clinical research.


Processing of this data will be conducted in accordance with applicable law and within such purpose limitations as are notified to employees in Integra’s EU Employee Notification and the EU Safe Harbor Privacy Policy.
